</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="52D1C45E7F46BE6DCA100CCE561E9769" pageId="null" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="D23C4F6BA03B16CA60E8808E21470BDA" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">
Ausdauernde 
<normalizedToken id="8465CBF049D3F30D740B613112DDB7EA" originalValue="Kräuter" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Kraeuter</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="8781AEFAF6DFE25C73CBC9B9E49FABD9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">mit knolligem Rhizom.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="4463DCA720AC3B71C3ADD008079A5529" originalValue="Grundständige" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Grundstaendige</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="CBC88862BA004DDA9E4EEE273589C105" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
lang gestielt, tief 
<normalizedToken id="729F160FD896CE09E56C96BDFA22FE44" originalValue="radiär" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">radiaer</normalizedToken>
geteilt. 
<emphasis id="8D662A1A225521DF56D4DE99A328ADE0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">
<normalizedToken id="4608308340AE77B32E41A3B8476F18EE" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
3
</emphasis>
, sitzend, 
<normalizedToken id="CAEEC54EB1EC1DF17375A02CBE11336A" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
wie die 
<normalizedToken id="812892F4CD6665D8131665AB708ACB6E" originalValue="grundständigen" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">grundstaendigen</normalizedToken>
, unter der einzelnen, 
<normalizedToken id="76D06DBDB4CD77FC681E54D9EB7DC49F" originalValue="endständigen" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">endstaendigen</normalizedToken>
, aktinomorphen, zwittrigen 
<normalizedToken id="0E23AD1B3A17E5830ADF4179F34BA7E4" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Bluete</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="BCE6067776B66D4E91EC9B13AAD2FFC0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">
eine 
<normalizedToken id="C7177704EE226082706D9FD10BEBF1D2" originalValue="sternförmige" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">sternfoermige</normalizedToken>
Rosette bildend.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="0EFC1C809AE64E1B44AF558B8A80465F" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
meist 6, selten bis 10, 
<emphasis id="7008370632AA2189B8EEC35C3C6496E9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">kronblattartig, gelb.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="9D48F0544301AC7E8FAE2C19492AAD2C" originalValue="Honigblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Honigblaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="2728EF1E85DFA85E9429D89DB6B03417" originalValue="trichterförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">trichterfoermig</normalizedToken>
, gelb, 21ippig. 
<normalizedToken id="1FD92F5AF206980AEE9956C4E02BBC86" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
zahlreich. 
<emphasis id="D0A712A798DB96FCCB6BF06C06D0BFDE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Fruchtknoten 4-8, mehrsamig</emphasis>
, 
<normalizedToken id="15FA1E2958570ED05BAB83F97472BAD4" originalValue="geschnäbelt" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">geschnaebelt</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="42E86580C51C80CAF423D61B99B3B2EE" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">
Die Gattung 
<normalizedToken id="E07F34C375D90CF4780AEADB6AA3799F" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">umfasst</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="3834258F068624CD4B3BF236FDE3C7FC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">8 Arten</emphasis>
, die in West-, Zentral- und Ostasien verbreitet sind. 2 Arten, 
<taxonomicName id="5C1A6DA8BF24E3C2BF51DABA1BA0DE6F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Eranthis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hiemalis">
<emphasis id="4ADDDFAAC703DBDB4E1DAAF5FB15ABE9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">E. hiemalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<emphasis id="E090C8D232C9C14BFB5558B1E655A072" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">E. ciliaca</emphasis>
Schott et Kotschy sind in 
<normalizedToken id="80D390E208AE43DFE671F343DD843723" originalValue="Südeuropa" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Suedeuropa</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="C9EAC3958BAD917B6D189C679BDFF3DC" originalValue="ursprünglich" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">urspruenglich</normalizedToken>
, und 
<taxonomicName id="2BB2F53ABB9D710F3D8DF975921D094C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Eranthis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hiemalis">
<emphasis id="F0A2C661FD76A1C15FF87CEF830C1C16" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">E. hiemalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
wurde in West- und Zentraleuropa schon im 16. Jahrhundert angepflanzt.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="224124B64C322E378C97269E708AA02B" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">
Neuerdings werden nur die beiden 
<normalizedToken id="B5B5C969280DB0341C0A1ED570251DAC" originalValue="südeuropäischen" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">suedeuropaeischen</normalizedToken>
Arten in der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="9862DFD6B70F14FD7E64DF88D00942DB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Eranthis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87B2B1302F334F376CAD7447AE1208FF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Eranthis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belassen und die asiatischen Arten in die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="1A7E2C75AF8C872DF7FBB856C4185A3C" authority="Nakai" authorityName="Nakai" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Shibateranthis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05BC23F3232DC6B0304F6067B5D396BC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="36">Shibateranthis</emphasis>
Nakai
</taxonomicName>
gestellt (vgl. Janchen 1949).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
